claim.claim-text:
8. A method of overcurrent sensing, the method comprising:
generating an analog output signal representative of a sensed AC current;
generating a digital representation of the analog output signal using a plurality of discrete samples;
determining those of the plurality of discrete samples having a substantially identical magnitude, wherein the substantially identical magnitude is a maximum magnitude represented by the digital representation; and
estimating an amount of overcurrent in the sensed AC current by evaluating those of the plurality of discrete samples that have the substantially identical magnitude.
